      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNSEEN RULER (6) hasn't won for a long time but has continued to savage the line back in Victoria against stronger opposition. Has been kept fresh for this with 36 days between runs. If he's close enough at the turn he will prove more than a handful to hold out. KHOR (2) made light work of his rivals last start in the Edenhope Cup, putting 3.5L to second. Meets a few of these 2.5kgs worse, though doubt that's enough for them to turn the tables. ROYAL MILE (4) returned to somewhere near his best last start when dominating a BM68 at Murray Bridge, snapping a 4+ year drought out of the winner's circle. If he can hold that form, he's right up to this. PITTSBURGH PIRATE (1) loves a country cup and gets his chance to add another to the resume. Don't dismiss third-up.",
